entry.title: Russia Blames Ukraine, U.K. for Collapse of Grain Deal
entry.content: Moscow said wreckage it recovered from a drone strike on the occupied Black Sea port of Sevastopol proves the attack was mounted with British assistance, a claim the U.K. denies.

entry.title: Where Are the Air Bags? Russia's Hobbled Auto Industry Struggles to Reboot
entry.content: The business is shaping up to be an early test case for the Russian economy and sanctions make it more difficult to find parts; ‘a brutal car’

entry.title: Aung SanSuuKyi's Life in Myanmar Prison: No Visitors, Calls or News
entry.content: The Nobel Peace Prize winner has been sentenced to 26 years in a series of cases since the country’s military coup, and more trials are under way.
